WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:06.163
<i>NARRATOR: We lived in an electric world.
We relied on it for everything.</i>

00:06.381 --> 00:07.963
<i>And then the power went out.</i>

00:08.383 --> 00:11.375
<i>Everything stopped working.
We weren't prepared.</i>

00:11.637 --> 00:14.379
<i>Fear and confusion led to panic.</i>

00:14.598 --> 00:16.714
<i>The lucky ones made it out of the cities.</i>

00:16.934 --> 00:19.596
<i>The government collapsed.
Militias took over...</i>

00:19.811 --> 00:22.553
<i>...controlling the food supply
and stockpiling weapons.</i>

00:22.981 --> 00:25.689
<i>We still don't know
why the power went out.</i>

00:25.984 --> 00:28.897
<i>But we're hopeful that someone
will come and light the way.</i>

00:30.280 --> 00:31.770
<i>Previously on Revolution:</i>

00:31.990 --> 00:34.072
- I gotta go get Nora.
- Who is this woman?

00:34.284 --> 00:35.649
She's really good at blowing stuff up.

00:35.911 --> 00:37.493
- Joined the rebels?
- What rebels?

00:37.704 --> 00:39.866
- Bunch of bleeding heart--
- Patriots.

00:40.123 --> 00:41.579
[WHITAKER GRUNTS]

00:41.792 --> 00:43.328
Captain Tom Neville.
Know him?

00:43.585 --> 00:45.417
- He was here.
- He have a prisoner with him?

00:45.629 --> 00:47.415
A boy. Nineteen. Blond hair.

00:47.673 --> 00:49.630
MILES: And you saw him when?
- Yesterday.

00:50.050 --> 00:52.337
Danny's close.
We can maybe catch up by tomorrow.

00:52.553 --> 00:53.588
You're joking.

00:53.804 --> 00:56.216
MILES: How long you been following us?
- Long enough. Just noticed?

00:56.431 --> 00:58.422
- You must be getting old.
- He's a spy.

00:59.309 --> 01:02.768
I'm sorry. But you're important, kid.
More important than you even know.

01:02.980 --> 01:04.470
[GRUNTING]

01:05.315 --> 01:07.807
CHARLIE: How is she?
- You saved me, Charlie.

01:08.318 --> 01:11.436
That's right. We're here to save you.
Maggie, please don't go. Maggie...

01:11.655 --> 01:13.316
[SOBBING]

01:15.993 --> 01:17.700
[MEN CHEERING AND LAUGHING,
THEN FOOT THUDS]

01:17.911 --> 01:19.618
MAN 1: Ugh!
MAN 2: Oh, nice.

01:19.830 --> 01:20.865
[LAUGHS]

01:22.749 --> 01:23.864
MAN 2: How you feel?
MAN 1: Ugh.

01:25.752 --> 01:26.787
[MAN 1 GROANING]

01:27.004 --> 01:28.711
TOM:
You got some more?

01:29.715 --> 01:32.127
Aw. Come on, who's next?

01:33.343 --> 01:35.084
Danny b0)'-

01:35.387 --> 01:37.344
You're up.

01:37.681 --> 01:39.843
- No-- No, thanks.
TOM: Come on.

01:40.392 --> 01:42.554
These boot-licks
are too afraid to hit hard.

01:42.769 --> 01:44.635
But I know how you feel about me.

01:48.191 --> 01:49.306
I'm not gonna fight you.

01:49.526 --> 01:51.062
[TOM GRUNTS AND MEN LAUGH]

01:55.198 --> 01:57.235
You gotta toughen up, son.

01:57.451 --> 01:58.691
[BONES CRACKS AND DANNY GASPING]

02:08.753 --> 02:09.788
[TOM CHUCKLES]

02:11.882 --> 02:12.997
[TOM GRUNTS]

02:14.676 --> 02:16.917
Atta boy. Atta boy.

02:18.722 --> 02:19.928
[BOTH GRUNTING AND MEN SHOUTING

02:34.404 --> 02:35.565
[BLOOD SPLATTERS]

02:46.041 --> 02:47.907
Can you explain that?

02:50.796 --> 02:54.005
TOM: The Connolly family. Fire claim.
- Uh-huh.

02:54.216 --> 02:57.083
- And the property damage?
- That was-- Well...

02:57.302 --> 03:00.340
How many times have we had
a conversation like this?

03:01.598 --> 03:05.432
They're not covered for smoke damage,
so we don't pay for smoke damage.

03:07.104 --> 03:08.310
You're fired.

03:33.046 --> 03:34.332
All right, come on.

03:35.590 --> 03:38.457
Just give them a minute.

03:39.136 --> 03:40.467
I just gave them 30.

03:41.096 --> 03:43.053
That's plenty. It's time to go.

03:43.265 --> 03:45.472
Miles, stop it.

03:46.476 --> 03:48.092
We've lost too much time already.

03:48.311 --> 03:51.599
We just buried Maggie,
so please let us say goodbye.

03:51.815 --> 03:53.522
Goodbye?

03:53.900 --> 03:55.356
To who?

03:55.569 --> 03:58.311
That's just a body in the ground, Charlie.

03:58.572 --> 04:00.734
But, Danny, he's still alive.

04:01.366 --> 04:03.198
And he's close.

04:04.578 --> 04:08.162
And if you want him back, you can't
do this. You don't have the luxury.

04:11.418 --> 04:14.080
But hanging around here crying...

04:14.296 --> 04:15.912
...it's not gonna help.

04:19.009 --> 04:20.625
Let's move.

04:25.223 --> 04:26.884
I'm sorry about Maggie.

05:09.976 --> 05:11.011
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

05:13.063 --> 05:14.144
What was that?

05:19.569 --> 05:21.435
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

05:36.336 --> 05:37.371
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

05:38.797 --> 05:43.416
If Monroe has got a train, it's bad, Charlie.
It could be real bad.

05:43.677 --> 05:47.420
- What do you mean, "a few snags"?
- This should be in a museum, not on tracks.

05:47.639 --> 05:50.427
Tracks, by the way,
they're working day and night to clear.

05:50.642 --> 05:53.384
Prying every busted car off
between here and Philadelphia.

05:53.603 --> 05:57.221
The train is due to leave
first thing tomorrow. Yes?

05:57.816 --> 06:02.401
So if I were you,
quit making excuses and make my deadline.

06:02.863 --> 06:05.150
- Yes, sir.
- See you bright and early.

06:05.365 --> 06:06.696
Yeah.

06:06.908 --> 06:10.367
All right, you heard the man.
Let's move it!

06:13.039 --> 06:14.825
<i>MONROE".
Your son is boarding the train...</i>

06:16.126 --> 06:17.332
...and he'll be here soon.

06:21.131 --> 06:23.042
Rachel, come on. This is good news.

06:23.258 --> 06:24.623
How is this good news?

06:25.260 --> 06:28.924
Well, you can be with your boy again,
and you can be happy again.

06:30.724 --> 06:32.055
Bass...

06:35.186 --> 06:36.722
...please.

06:37.814 --> 06:39.350
We used to be friends.

06:40.442 --> 06:43.651
If that means anything to you...

06:44.070 --> 06:46.186
...let Danny go.

06:46.823 --> 06:48.405
You have me.

06:51.369 --> 06:53.701
I'll tell you everything.

06:57.834 --> 06:59.495
I know.

07:01.671 --> 07:03.662
I know you will.

07:04.799 --> 07:07.666
And you know how I know?

07:10.263 --> 07:12.550
Because I'm gonna have your son
here with me.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.387
You're a son of a bitch.

07:20.607 --> 07:23.941
I gave you a lot of chances to cooperate.

07:25.403 --> 07:26.939
I'm sorry it's come to this.

07:47.217 --> 07:48.252
[ALL CHATTERING]

08:07.696 --> 08:09.528
MAN:
What're you standing around for, lady?

08:09.739 --> 08:11.980
This train is leaving
first thing in the morning.

08:16.997 --> 08:19.159
NORA:
And Monroe, with a working train...

08:19.374 --> 08:22.082
...makes him dangerous, Miles,
even more so than usual.

08:22.293 --> 08:25.376
I know.
We got other problems right now.

08:25.714 --> 08:27.250
- So?
- Train leaves tomorrow.

08:27.757 --> 08:30.044
Let me guess, going to Philly, right?

08:30.260 --> 08:33.048
They're putting Danny on that train,
I guarantee it.

08:36.390 --> 08:40.100
How about you, militia boy?
You know about any of this?

08:42.188 --> 08:43.222
Yeah.

08:44.524 --> 08:46.060
Danny's here somewhere.

08:46.276 --> 08:49.018
If we don't find him by morning,
he's gone.

08:49.237 --> 08:51.148
We should check if he's on the train.

08:51.364 --> 08:55.323
And outside that, they're probably
holding him in a cell somewhere.

08:55.827 --> 08:58.364
That's what I'd do.
So we check the old station house.

08:58.580 --> 09:01.163
Could be a walk-in freezer,
meat locker. I don't know.

09:01.416 --> 09:02.827
Anything secure.

09:03.293 --> 09:05.409
No. No crossbows, no swords.

09:05.628 --> 09:07.915
We gotta keep a low profile.

09:08.506 --> 09:11.840
You, guard Nipples. He even tries
to move, go ahead and shoot him.

09:12.343 --> 09:14.300
We split up, we canvass the town.

09:14.512 --> 09:17.675
You even catch a scent of Danny,
walk away.

09:18.016 --> 09:20.804
Come find me.
We only get one shot at this.

09:47.754 --> 09:50.337
You probably
don't remember banks.

09:51.716 --> 09:53.878
It was strange.

09:54.260 --> 09:57.252
I used to work my fingers to the bone...

09:57.472 --> 09:59.258
...for money.

10:01.184 --> 10:02.219
Ah.

10:02.852 --> 10:04.968
Never even saw what I made.

10:06.064 --> 10:09.056
- Yeah, I'll tell you something else.
- Shut up already.

10:11.152 --> 10:13.063
What did you say to me?

10:13.279 --> 10:15.145
I'm sick of it.

10:15.740 --> 10:17.777
I'm sick of your weird speeches.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.949
Your mind games.

10:20.161 --> 10:23.699
Whatever you're trying to do,
it's not working.

10:25.125 --> 10:27.833
I would be very...

10:28.169 --> 10:30.160
...very careful, if I were you.

10:31.089 --> 10:32.625
Or what?

10:33.341 --> 10:35.127
Are you gonna hit me again?

10:36.261 --> 10:40.505
Does that make you feel tough,
beating up an 18-year-old kid?

10:41.099 --> 10:43.340
What's that say about you?

10:48.106 --> 10:50.268
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS
AND PEOPLE SHOUTING]

11:07.458 --> 11:08.573
Hey, there, Rob.

11:08.793 --> 11:12.252
You think that maybe you could
keep your music down at night?

11:12.463 --> 11:14.374
It keeps my son awake.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.934
- Daddy.
- Hey.

11:32.150 --> 11:33.311
[TOM LAUGHS]

11:34.194 --> 11:36.526
Hey, Optimus.

11:36.779 --> 11:37.814
How you guys dOinQ?

11:38.031 --> 11:39.772
- Good, Daddy.
- Good.

11:44.913 --> 11:47.780
- Hey.
- Hey, how was work?

11:49.167 --> 11:52.080
Oh, good. You know, just fine.

11:52.795 --> 11:55.036
Hey, uh, have I got some time before dinner?

11:55.506 --> 11:56.917
Yeah, a little bit. Why?

11:59.469 --> 12:00.504
[GRUNTING]

12:18.529 --> 12:19.940
Hey, Jason.

12:21.699 --> 12:23.690
How long you been there?

12:25.036 --> 12:26.902
- You wanna take a swing?
- Can I?

12:27.121 --> 12:28.737
Sure. Come on.

12:30.583 --> 12:31.869
Okay-

12:32.085 --> 12:34.577
Hands up. Now, just remember...

12:34.796 --> 12:37.709
...we only hit the bag,
we never hit people.

12:44.555 --> 12:46.137
Honey?

12:47.850 --> 12:50.091
Did the power go out?

12:51.354 --> 12:52.389
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

13:23.970 --> 13:25.005
[RINGS]

13:26.431 --> 13:28.798
- Hi.
HUTCH: Hello.

13:30.601 --> 13:32.808
Can I help you with something?

13:33.021 --> 13:35.433
Yeah.
A friend told me about this place.

13:36.065 --> 13:38.773
I'm looking for a biography of Joe Biden.

13:48.703 --> 13:49.738
[GASPS]

13:51.122 --> 13:53.329
I just need to be sure.

13:56.544 --> 13:58.160
Okay-

13:59.922 --> 14:01.458
Now show me yours.

14:12.727 --> 14:14.388
Nora Clayton.

14:14.604 --> 14:17.312
Hutch. Ken Hutchinson.

14:21.444 --> 14:23.776
So how many men you got
around here, Hutch?

14:23.988 --> 14:29.404
Well, uh, you are looking at the entirety
of Noblesville underground.

14:30.411 --> 14:32.948
- You're joking.
- No.

14:33.331 --> 14:36.039
The militia wiped out our whole unit.

14:36.626 --> 14:38.242
My wife along with them.

14:40.963 --> 14:42.704
It's just me now.

14:43.341 --> 14:47.426
No, it's you and me.
And we're gonna blow up that train.

14:50.556 --> 14:51.591
[ALL CHATTERING]

15:11.035 --> 15:13.197
Excuse me, young lady.

15:14.122 --> 15:16.489
If you don't mind me asking,
what are you doing?

15:17.208 --> 15:20.291
Because it looks like
you're casing the joint.

15:21.045 --> 15:22.080
[CHUCKLES]

15:23.005 --> 15:25.121
I'm spying.

15:26.384 --> 15:28.671
Um, it's my boyfriend.

15:29.137 --> 15:30.878
No, don't look.

15:31.764 --> 15:34.381
Here.

15:38.396 --> 15:40.387
I think he might be cheating on me.

15:42.150 --> 15:44.107
What's your name?

15:44.318 --> 15:45.683
Sara McGill.

15:47.905 --> 15:49.737
Captain Tom Neville.

15:55.746 --> 15:58.408
CHARLIE: It's very nice to meet you,
Captain Neville.

15:59.917 --> 16:01.908
Are you here for the train?

16:02.587 --> 16:03.998
How'd you guess that?

16:05.131 --> 16:06.621
Well...

16:06.841 --> 16:10.300
...I mean, everyone's here
for the train, right?

16:10.928 --> 16:12.919
I suppose so.

16:14.432 --> 16:16.548
You have a nice afternoon.

16:20.938 --> 16:22.929
And if I may...

16:23.816 --> 16:26.183
...that boy's a fool if he's two-timing you.

16:29.947 --> 16:31.483
You take care now.

17:01.521 --> 17:02.807
[GASPS THE GRUNTS]

17:03.022 --> 17:06.013
Think I can't spot a tail?
Especially one as clumsy as yours.

17:06.233 --> 17:09.226
Who are you?

17:09.529 --> 17:11.111
Okay, suit yourself.

17:11.321 --> 17:13.654
Unh! Get out of here!

17:14.617 --> 17:15.732
I should have guessed.

17:20.665 --> 17:22.531
Okay, then.

17:22.750 --> 17:24.582
So is this the sister?

17:27.797 --> 17:29.708
Quite the family resemblance.

17:29.924 --> 17:31.790
- She looks like Danny.
- I said go!

17:32.510 --> 17:34.672
[BOTH GRUNTING]

17:37.265 --> 17:38.847
Miles.

17:40.560 --> 17:42.142
Tom.

17:50.861 --> 17:52.226
How's the wife?

17:53.823 --> 17:55.484
Julia's good.

17:55.700 --> 17:58.112
I haven't seen her
in about a year of course.

17:58.327 --> 17:59.988
Yeah, I've been out looking for you.

18:00.413 --> 18:03.280
But we write. Her azaleas are in bloom.

18:04.542 --> 18:07.830
- How's my nephew?
- Oh, he's a spirited young man.

18:08.129 --> 18:10.040
[BOTH GRUNT]

18:10.548 --> 18:11.834
Where is he?

18:12.258 --> 18:14.841
Oh, like that's just
what I'm gonna do, Miles.

18:15.219 --> 18:17.460
Spread my legs
and show you everything.

18:19.515 --> 18:21.802
Okay, how about a trade?

18:22.560 --> 18:25.177
Danny, for one of your guys.

18:26.022 --> 18:30.858
- You got one of my guys?
- Yeah. The one who's been tailing us...

18:31.068 --> 18:34.402
...the, uh, short hair, shirt too tight.

18:35.489 --> 18:37.105
You can keep him.

18:37.325 --> 18:40.613
- I'll kill him, Tom. You know I will.
- You do what you gotta do.

18:40.828 --> 18:42.034
I got new orders.

18:42.413 --> 18:45.997
I need Danny.
Hell, maybe more than I need you.

18:48.461 --> 18:51.203
Look, while we're talking...

18:51.422 --> 18:53.459
...I wanna ask you something.

18:54.800 --> 18:56.586
Why'd you leave?

18:58.512 --> 18:59.968
You wouldn't understand.

19:00.181 --> 19:01.216
[SCOFFS]

19:01.682 --> 19:02.797
Hey!

19:03.017 --> 19:04.052
[SHOUTING]

19:06.479 --> 19:09.972
- I gotta go, Tom.
- But you just got here.

19:10.191 --> 19:12.148
[BOTH GRUNTING]

19:14.445 --> 19:15.480
[SHOUTING]

19:40.429 --> 19:42.466
Can I have that back?

19:43.724 --> 19:45.886
That's an ugly necklace, my man.

19:48.354 --> 19:49.640
Yeah.

19:50.064 --> 19:52.055
It was my wife's.

20:07.039 --> 20:08.074
[METAL CLANGS]

20:18.884 --> 20:20.215
[DOOR OPENS]

20:21.762 --> 20:22.923
Oh, God.

20:23.264 --> 20:26.757
Nora. Uh-- Uh-- Who is this?

20:27.309 --> 20:28.549
Hutch.

20:28.769 --> 20:32.137
- You two know each other?
- He's resistance.

20:32.606 --> 20:35.815
Oh, so you have, like, what,
a secret handshake or something?

20:36.026 --> 20:39.690
Nora. Nora, what is going on?
Nora? Nor--

20:42.158 --> 20:44.274
Hutch, can you give us a minute?

20:44.493 --> 20:45.858
Aaron.

20:47.955 --> 20:50.743
You gotta warn Miles.
I'm putting a bomb on that train.

20:51.751 --> 20:54.083
- Well, what about Danny?
- This is more important.

20:54.462 --> 20:55.827
More important?

20:56.046 --> 20:57.912
There's gonna be dozens
of officers on board.

20:58.507 --> 21:01.670
So I have to blow it up
so a bunch of those bastards go down.

21:01.886 --> 21:06.130
And what if Danny is on board too?
What happens then?

21:08.559 --> 21:09.970
Miles will find him first.

21:10.519 --> 21:11.850
Miles has to find him first.

21:17.985 --> 21:20.147
Hey. What did I tell you?

21:20.362 --> 21:23.104
What did I say? Did I say not get close?
Do not get close.

21:23.324 --> 21:24.814
He bumped into me.

21:25.034 --> 21:29.278
You followed him. You were over your head.
You have no idea how dangerous he is.

21:29.497 --> 21:31.955
Okay, I get it, I screwed up.
But it's Neville.

21:32.166 --> 21:34.703
- He has Danny. I just--
- You got emotional!

21:34.919 --> 21:36.626
And you panicked, and you blew it.

21:38.964 --> 21:42.457
Surprise was the only thing we had going,
and you pissed it away.

21:42.718 --> 21:44.300
This was already hard.

21:44.512 --> 21:46.628
You just made it impossible.

21:46.847 --> 21:49.930
If we don't get Danny back,
you got nobody to blame but yourself.

21:50.142 --> 21:51.758
Why are you--?

21:53.938 --> 21:56.646
You never used to be like this.

21:58.150 --> 21:59.936
How do you know?

22:01.612 --> 22:04.195
Because I remember you.

22:07.451 --> 22:09.909
It hit me the other day.

22:10.579 --> 22:12.661
I was about 4.

22:13.082 --> 22:15.369
And you came for a visit.

22:16.085 --> 22:19.203
And you took me for a ride in your car.
You had one of those--

22:19.421 --> 22:20.957
One of those tape decks.

22:23.050 --> 22:27.795
And you were singing at the top
of your lungs, and I remember laughing.

22:34.979 --> 22:37.437
What happened to that guy?

22:43.028 --> 22:44.689
He's dead.

22:53.080 --> 22:55.412
- Sir, it's all taken care of.
- Good.

22:55.624 --> 22:56.705
DANNY:
Don't touch me.

22:57.334 --> 22:58.745
Where are we going?

22:59.837 --> 23:02.044
- A more secure location.
- Sir, we gotta go.

23:02.256 --> 23:04.873
What happened out there?
If I didn't know any better...

23:05.092 --> 23:07.174
...I'd say that you look a little nervous.

23:07.469 --> 23:09.881
Do I need to repeat myself?

23:13.434 --> 23:14.469
[MEN SHOUTING]

23:22.234 --> 23:24.350
I think we have to go.

23:25.070 --> 23:27.402
Just on foot? Just walk out of here?

23:27.615 --> 23:31.609
There are looters, people shooting each
other for a bag of chips. It's dangerous.

23:31.827 --> 23:35.195
Well, what makes you think
it's not too dangerous to stay?

23:36.081 --> 23:37.913
[GLASS SHATTERS]

23:38.125 --> 23:41.834
- No, baby, no--
- No, no, no. You just stay here. Stay here.

23:53.307 --> 23:54.342
[SILVERWARE CLANKING]

23:57.853 --> 23:59.810
- Rob?
- Walk away, Tom.

24:00.022 --> 24:03.185
This is my house. You're my neighbor.

24:03.442 --> 24:07.731
- Daddy?
- Jason, go back to bed.

24:08.906 --> 24:11.944
You too, Tom,
before I beat you in front of your son.

24:15.663 --> 24:16.994
[BOTH GRUNTING]

24:25.839 --> 24:27.295
Daddy.

24:29.009 --> 24:30.499
[GASPING]

24:41.271 --> 24:42.761
Tom!

25:08.674 --> 25:11.382
CHARLIE: She's gonna blow up the train?
What if Danny's on board?

25:11.593 --> 25:14.301
- She said she didn't have a choice.
- We have to stop her.

25:14.513 --> 25:16.470
You won't be able to find her.

25:17.975 --> 25:21.468
What we need to do is find Danny,
if we can.

25:27.401 --> 25:28.436
[NATE GRUNTS]

25:32.156 --> 25:36.491
If you know anything about where they're
keeping my brother, you have to tell me.

25:36.702 --> 25:38.363
This is my family.

25:40.706 --> 25:46.577
I'm asking, I'm begging you,
please, tell me.

25:52.259 --> 25:53.920
I'm sorry.

25:54.678 --> 25:56.214
I can't help you.

25:58.766 --> 26:01.224
Well, then I can't help you either.

26:09.526 --> 26:10.561
[NATE GRUNTING]

26:17.826 --> 26:19.282
MILES:
Damn it.

26:42.559 --> 26:43.594
[BELL TOLLING]

26:44.686 --> 26:47.724
JOHN: The Georgia Federation formed
an alliance with the Plains Nation...

26:47.940 --> 26:50.557
...amassing troops along our borders
to the south and west.

26:50.776 --> 26:54.360
The skirmish has flared up here,
just outside of St. Louis.

26:54.780 --> 26:56.942
We lost a few hundred men.

26:57.157 --> 27:00.741
So where did those sons of bitches
get the stones all of a sudden?

27:01.036 --> 27:04.324
We assume they heard about
our rebel problems.

27:04.915 --> 27:06.997
They think we can't keep
our house in order.

27:07.543 --> 27:09.580
They see a chance to exploit weakness.

27:11.421 --> 27:15.915
- Sorry, sir, I didn't mean to imply--
- Quit apologizing, John.

27:21.515 --> 27:23.802
Give me one Black Hawk chopper.
Just one.

27:25.561 --> 27:27.643
What would they do then, huh?

27:27.855 --> 27:29.892
Throw stones at it?

27:31.233 --> 27:32.723
No.

27:33.944 --> 27:38.939
No, they'd kneel and bow,
just like the Mayans before the Spanish.

27:40.951 --> 27:43.534
And I'll still cut their guts out.

27:45.664 --> 27:50.454
By the time we're done here, John,
North America is ours.

27:51.253 --> 27:53.290
Sky is the limit.

27:58.552 --> 27:59.587
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

28:01.430 --> 28:05.674
The problem with bombs these days
is the ignition.

28:05.976 --> 28:10.721
Electric charges are impossible,
fuses are unreliable. But this...

28:11.565 --> 28:15.604
...the train is on the move,
the log gets tossed into the furnace...

28:15.819 --> 28:18.106
...and they ignite it for us.

28:18.322 --> 28:19.357
Bang.

28:21.617 --> 28:24.609
It couldn't have been easy
setting up that first one.

28:26.580 --> 28:28.787
Knowing what it was gonna do.

28:28.999 --> 28:33.459
Doesn't get any easier.
You just get better at swallowing it.

28:36.423 --> 28:38.790
My wife, she was the fighter.

28:39.009 --> 28:43.594
Me, I was happy burying myself
in my books.

28:44.223 --> 28:46.760
But doing something like this...

28:48.852 --> 28:51.059
...I think she'd be proud.

28:53.982 --> 28:56.144
Yeah, she'd be proud.

29:27.724 --> 29:30.682
MILES:
Can't believe I didn't think of this before.

29:38.986 --> 29:42.149
A bank vault. The perfect place
to keep Danny.

29:42.990 --> 29:45.322
MAN:
It's just that 24 hours was a stretch.

29:45.534 --> 29:48.947
And you want us to leave now?
I mean, who knows if she'll even make it.

29:49.162 --> 29:51.403
Then you'll push her
into Philadelphia yourself.

29:51.623 --> 29:53.705
- Clear?
- Clear.

29:53.917 --> 29:55.123
Captain.

29:55.335 --> 29:58.873
Matheson's gonna be here,
so why are we running away?

30:07.347 --> 30:08.758
[ALL SHOUTING]

30:11.226 --> 30:12.261
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

30:16.189 --> 30:18.351
When did you say it was leaving?

30:18.900 --> 30:20.937
First thing tomorrow.

30:50.599 --> 30:51.839
That's Captain Neville.

30:57.272 --> 31:00.606
If Neville is on that train,
then that kid has to be Danny.

31:03.987 --> 31:06.945
- Damn it.
- What? What's wrong?

31:08.116 --> 31:10.824
- I can't do this. I gotta get that bomb off.
- What?

31:11.036 --> 31:14.870
I made a promise. And this kid, if he dies--
Hutch, this one, I can't swallow.

31:15.082 --> 31:16.698
Nora.

31:17.042 --> 31:18.077
You were right.

31:18.293 --> 31:19.909
We have to do this.

31:20.128 --> 31:21.459
I know I said I could.

31:21.671 --> 31:24.254
- But now I just-- I can't do it.
- I have to do it.

31:24.466 --> 31:26.798
I have to do it for my wife.
She died for this.

31:27.010 --> 31:28.045
Hutch, get out of my--

31:28.261 --> 31:29.467
[KNIFE SLICES THEN NORA GROANS]

31:38.772 --> 31:40.354
I'm sorry.

31:40.607 --> 31:42.518
I'm sorry.

31:57.457 --> 31:58.947
NORA:
I tried to stop it.

32:02.295 --> 32:03.706
Nora?

32:06.550 --> 32:08.666
- Who did this to you?
NORA: Listen.

32:08.927 --> 32:10.918
The bomb is on the train.

32:12.347 --> 32:13.678
And so is your brother.

32:28.196 --> 32:32.030
The bomb is a hollowed-out log.
It's in front of the tender car, Miles.

32:32.534 --> 32:34.024
I'm sorry.

32:42.752 --> 32:43.833
MILES:
Charlie.

33:02.731 --> 33:03.766
[GRUNTS]

33:09.571 --> 33:10.732
[CHARLIE SCREAMS THEN GRUNTS]

33:44.439 --> 33:47.773
I'll get the bomb, you go find Danny.

33:57.118 --> 33:58.153
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

34:21.935 --> 34:23.141
[MOUTHS]
Charlie.

34:40.411 --> 34:42.197
[DAN NY GRUNTS]

34:53.757 --> 34:54.873
[BOTH GRUNTING]

34:55.092 --> 34:56.174
[CHARLIE GRUNTS]

34:58.513 --> 34:59.628
[BOTH GRUNTING]

35:02.601 --> 35:04.512
[BOTH GRUNTING]

35:04.728 --> 35:06.344
Danny!

35:11.276 --> 35:12.516
[CHARLIE GRUNTING]

35:14.321 --> 35:15.777
[METAL BANGING]

35:18.533 --> 35:20.149
[CHARLIE YELLS]

35:22.370 --> 35:24.202
[CHARLIE GRUNTING]

35:34.507 --> 35:35.542
[GASPING]

35:41.389 --> 35:42.720
[GRUNTS]

35:47.312 --> 35:49.553
Come on. Let's go.

35:50.732 --> 35:52.018
No! Let me go!

35:52.233 --> 35:53.644
Let me go!

36:08.416 --> 36:09.577
You bring the girl to me.

36:10.543 --> 36:13.160
Bring her to me.
I'm gonna shoot the bitch.

36:15.674 --> 36:17.164
That's an order.

36:18.843 --> 36:21.926
- Now.
- Shield your head.

36:24.974 --> 36:26.464
[CHARLIE SCREAMS THEN GRUNTING]

36:57.507 --> 37:00.124
I told you to bring me the girl.

37:41.217 --> 37:44.084
- You gonna be all right?
NORA: I'm doing better.

37:44.304 --> 37:46.841
Didn't hit anything too important.

37:48.683 --> 37:51.425
- Miles, if you hadn't gotten that bomb--
- But I did.

38:12.165 --> 38:14.497
That uncle you knew
when you were little...

38:16.878 --> 38:18.710
...he's not dead.

38:21.049 --> 38:23.040
I just, um...

38:24.135 --> 38:27.378
I can't be him right now...

38:28.056 --> 38:31.094
...because I'm gonna have to kill Monroe.

38:31.309 --> 38:34.552
I'm gonna have to walk to Philly
and kill my best friend.

38:36.272 --> 38:38.309
I get it, Miles.

38:39.192 --> 38:41.229
But honestly, I don't wanna hear it.

38:41.653 --> 38:44.065
You were right. Sitting here moping...

38:44.781 --> 38:48.820
...it won't help get us Danny back
and it probably will get us killed.

38:50.829 --> 38:53.696
So, Philadelphia.

38:53.915 --> 38:55.906
Aaron, you coming?

38:58.378 --> 38:59.868
Yes, I'm coming.

39:01.422 --> 39:05.006
Nora, you in,
or you gonna try to kill my brother again?

39:07.595 --> 39:09.211
I'm in.

39:09.430 --> 39:10.886
Good.

39:11.599 --> 39:13.385
Miles, you?

39:16.104 --> 39:19.392
All right, let's get going.
We got a lot of ground to cover.

39:22.610 --> 39:24.726
Nice job, coach.

40:07.822 --> 40:09.404
JULIA:
Jason.

40:09.991 --> 40:13.655
Hello, Mother. It's good to be home.

40:27.467 --> 40:29.959
TOM:
I'm gonna teach you how to use this.

40:31.429 --> 40:33.841
Gun too, when the time comes.

40:34.599 --> 40:36.260
Dad, I'm scared.

40:36.684 --> 40:38.470
I love you, Jason.

40:38.686 --> 40:40.677
But we have to toughen up.

40:40.897 --> 40:45.607
If we're scared, if we're weak,
then we're dead.

40:45.818 --> 40:47.183
Do you understand me?

40:54.869 --> 40:55.904
[ALL CHATTERING]

41:00.333 --> 41:01.539
RACHEL:
He's hurt.

41:02.794 --> 41:04.785
What did they do to him?

41:05.213 --> 41:08.046
From now on,
no one will touch him, Rachel.

41:09.050 --> 41:11.462
And you can see him
any time you want.

41:11.678 --> 41:14.545
As long as I tell you whatever you want.

41:15.014 --> 41:20.555
Well, if I help you, then you help me.

41:23.231 --> 41:24.938
Rachel.

41:25.650 --> 41:27.732
For the last time...

41:28.987 --> 41:31.228
...what was Ben working on?

41:49.924 --> 41:51.665
We were both working on it.

41:53.094 --> 41:54.710
We worked together.

41:54.971 --> 41:57.759
I don't have all the specs...

41:58.016 --> 42:00.758
...but if you want
to turn the power back on...

42:01.728 --> 42:04.595
...it starts with these pendants.

42:08.901 --> 42:11.609
There are 12 of them.

42:48.941 --> 42:50.932
[English - US - SDH]
